[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged over fatal head-on crash in Scarisbrick

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with causing death by dangerous driving after a man was killed in a head-on crash.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Andrew Birch, 46, of Skelmersdale, Lancashire, died when his Peugeot was in collision with a Toyota on Southport Road, Scarisbrick, on 6 January.
Mr Birch's 80-year-old mother and a 41-year-old woman who was driving the Toyota were seriously injured.
Kenneth Grisedale, 56, of Hartwood Road, Southport, is due at Ormskirk Magistrates' Court on 25 August.
